<section id="about-us" class="emerald">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2 class="text-center">About The College<h2>
        <p class="text-justify" style="font-size:15px">
          St.Joseph’s Institute of  Technology, a St.Joseph’s group of Institutions  started  in  the  year  2011.It is a  Christian  Minority  Institution   with   six  streams  viz CSE,  EEE, ECE,   IT , MECH & CIVIL.
          The college has best infrastructure spread across 4 lakhs sq.ft with well equipped laboratories, workshops   and   classrooms.
          A    state   of    the   art   infrastructure   including  auditorium, mess  halls, administrative  block   covering  an area of  10 lakhs sq.ft.  is upcoming.
					Our  college  as  one  of  the  leading  engineering colleges,  focuses  on  inculcating   not  only   knowledge but  also   good   ethics   to   the  budding  engineers   of  future    India.
          This   proves   to be the uniqueness   of St. Joseph’s Institute of Technology.
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-center">Conference Theme<h2>
        <p class="text-justify" style="font-size:15px">First International Conference on “Recent Trends in Engineering and
          First International Conference on Recent Trends in Engineering and Technology is being
          organized by the various departments of St. Joseph’s Institute of Technology. The primary
          goal of the conference is to promote research and developmental activities in the recent trends
          in engineering and technology. It also helps to unite the great minds who believe in the need,
          for a technologically literate society. This conference on the recent trends in engineering and
          technology promises enormous potential to stimulate educational opportunities to the
          researchers, academicians and post graduate students. It is a powerful tool for the educators to
          interact with their peers, share knowledge and ideas. It also offers innovative technical
          resources to support professional learning for educators and education leaders. The one day
          conference comprises of keynote speeches and paper presentations in different sessions. It
          also provides the participants with the prospect of getting acquainted with the Recent Trends
          in Engineering and Technology, which helps in updating their knowledge thereby upgrading
          their organization and the overall Computer Society.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
